# User Modes Rules (用户模式)

ScrollCap has 3 modes: `.standard`, `.minor`, `.elder`. Every new feature MUST work correctly in ALL modes.

## How to read current mode

```swift
@Environment(\.userMode) private var userMode
```

## Minor Mode (未成年模式)

### What to hide/block

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - check shouldHidePayment for anything payment-related
if !appState.shouldHidePayment {
    ProUpgradeTeaser()
}

// ✅ GOOD - block payment deep links
case "payment":
    guard !appState.shouldHidePayment else { return }

// ❌ BAD - showing payment UI without checking
PaywallView()  // minor can see and purchase
```

### Rules

- **Payment**: ALL entry points to payment/Pro features must check `appState.shouldHidePayment`
- **External links**: Hide URLs, source code links, social media in minor mode
- **Edit tools**: Restrict advanced editing tools if `userMode == .minor`
- **Usage timer**: `AppState.checkUsageTime()` is called every 60s; show `UsageTimerBanner` when triggered

### Checklist for new features

- [ ] Does it involve payment? → guard with `shouldHidePayment`
- [ ] Does it link externally? → hide in minor mode
- [ ] Is it an advanced feature? → consider whether to restrict

## Elder Mode (适老化模式)

### Text & Touch

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - adaptive sizing
.frame(width: userMode == .elder ? 64 : 48, height: userMode == .elder ? 56 : 44)

// ✅ GOOD - padding for bigger touch targets
.padding(userMode == .elder ? 8 : 4)
.contentShape(Circle())  // extend hit area

// ❌ BAD - fixed tiny targets
.frame(width: 20, height: 20)  // elder can't tap this
```

### Animation suppression

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - use shouldReduceMotion pattern
private var shouldReduceMotion: Bool { reduceMotion || userMode == .elder }

// then use it everywhere:
.animation(shouldReduceMotion ? nil : SCTheme.Animation.standard, value: state)
.scaleEffect(shouldReduceMotion ? 1.0 : (isHovered ? 1.03 : 1.0))

// ✅ GOOD - guard animated onAppear
.onAppear {
    guard !shouldReduceMotion else { return }
    withAnimation(.easeInOut(duration: 1.5).repeatForever(autoreverses: true)) { ... }
}

// ❌ BAD - unguarded animation
withAnimation(SCTheme.Animation.spring) { ... }  // elder sees bouncing
```

### Rules

- **Touch targets**: Minimum 44×44pt (Apple HIG), elder mode should be 56+ pt
- **Text**: `UserModeAdaptiveModifier` sets `.dynamicTypeSize(.xxxLarge)` — don't override with fixed font sizes
- **Animations**: Always combine `@Environment(\.accessibilityReduceMotion)` with `userMode == .elder`
- **Buttons**: Use `ElderButtonStyle()` or `ElderCaptureButton` in elder mode
- **Contrast**: Prefer `.primary` / `.secondary` semantic colors over low-opacity custom colors

### Checklist for new features

- [ ] All tap targets ≥ 44pt, elder ≥ 56pt
- [ ] All animations guarded with `shouldReduceMotion`
- [ ] Elder mode has larger/simpler UI variant or uses `ElderButtonStyle`
- [ ] No fixed small font sizes (use dynamic type)

## Environment injection

EVERY window/scene that hosts UI must inject user mode:

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - all three
WindowGroup { ContentView().environment(appState).environment(\.userMode, appState.userMode).applyUserMode(appState.userMode) }
Settings { SettingsView().environment(appState).environment(\.userMode, appState.userMode).applyUserMode(appState.userMode) }
MenuBarExtra { MenuBarView().environment(appState).environment(\.userMode, appState.userMode).applyUserMode(appState.userMode) }

// ❌ BAD - missing userMode (Settings/MenuBar won't respect elder/minor)
Settings { SettingsView().environment(appState) }
```
